nctions were taken: </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2697 improvement actions were set (re</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‐</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">training, replacing an operative, test equipment availability/calibration, documentation) </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">163 of these left the scheme without addressing the actions </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">55 cases were referred to the NAPIT Compliance Panel to consider sanctions (of these 18 were from complaint cases and the remainder were from other evidence of non</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‐</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">compliance) </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">26 of these had further improvement actions and conditions set (additional moni</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">toring, heightened inspection, specific training etc) </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">25 of these cases resulted in suspension </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">24 in total had membership withdrawn either with or without a period of suspension </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">0 removals were challenged in the appeals process </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Hence the 163 who cance</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">lled their own membership without addressing improvement actions plus the 2</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">4</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> actively removed by the compliance procedure gives 18</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">7</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> whose membership ended as a result of identified non</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‐</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">compliance.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">This figure represents 15% of the 1224 enterprises whose P</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">art P membership ended during 2013 the remaining 85% is made up of retirements, business closure, sole traders gaining employment in larger firms and simple non</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‐</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">renewal. Only a small number of these seem to have scheme</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‐</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">hopped, the majority are either genui</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">nely not trading or they continue to trade without being registered.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">NAPIT stance of Qualified Supervisor model</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">NAPIT’s scheme is based on the person who </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">attends site to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">inspect and test the installation being a Qualified Operative who is at least equiva</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">lent to the EAS Qualified Supervisor. Because we have a high proportion of micro</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‐</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">business this is still often one person.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The total number of Qualified Operatives is 12</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">235 within 9006 enterprises. 8134 operatives work for 8134 sole traders and micro</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">‐</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">companies (i.e. 1 per enterprise) and 4101 operatives work for 872 larger companies at an average of 4.7 per enterprise (excluding one very large scheme member gives an average of 3.2 qualified operatives per enterprise for the rest).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Number of Complaints</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">B</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ased on the last two </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">complaints </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">reports </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">to DCLG, the annual level of complaints </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">about electrical work </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">received by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">NAPIT </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">runs at a level of 1-in-5000 installations – of course scheme members themselves will receive and resolve the bulk of complaints with</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">out them being escalated to the scheme.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">31 complaints received</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">6 were unfounded</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">5 remain open in the resolution process</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">15 were resolved</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">3 were unresolved due to member non-cooperation (resulting in removal)</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0.1pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">2 were unresolved do to consumer appointing </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">other contractors</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">I hope you find this clarification of use, and would be happy to provide any further information that you would assist you further in this enquiry. Please do not hesitate to get in touch if this would be desirable.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">10 January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-f